<div><title type="x-gen">Mark 16</title><div osisID="Mark.16.0" type="x-gen"><chapter osisID="Mark.16" sID="gen26855" /><title subType="x-Chapter" type="sub">CHAPTER 16</title> </div><div type="x-milestone" subType="x-preverse" sID="pv1768" /><title subType="x-preverse" type="section">The Resurrection</title> <div type="x-milestone" subType="x-preverse" eID="pv1768" /><verse osisID="Mark.16.1"><note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.1.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.16.1-Mark.16.8">Mark 16:1-8</reference>: <hi type="italic"><reference osisRef="Matt.28.1-Matt.28.8">Matt 28:1-8</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.24.1-Luke.24.10">Luke 24:1-10</reference></hi>; <reference osisRef="John.20.1-John.20.8">John 20:1-8</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G4521">When the Sabbath</w> <w lemma="strong:G1230">was over</w>, <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.1.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.15.47">Mark 15:47</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G3137">Mary</w> <w lemma="strong:G3094">Magdalene</w>, <w lemma="strong:G3137">and Mary</w> the <transChange type="added">mother</transChange> of <note n="1" osisID="Mark.16.1.note.1" type="explanation">Or <hi type="italic">Jacob</hi></note><w lemma="strong:G2385">James</w>, <w lemma="strong:G4539">and Salome</w>, <note n="C" osisID="Mark.16.1.xref.C" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Luke.23.56">Luke 23:56</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.19.39-John.19.40">John 19:39f</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G59">bought</w> <w lemma="strong:G759">spices</w>, <w lemma="strong:G2443">so</w> <w lemma="strong:G2064">that they might come</w> <w lemma="strong:G218b">and anoint</w> Him. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.2"><w lemma="strong:G3029">Very</w> <w lemma="strong:G4404">early</w> <w lemma="strong:G1520">on the first</w> <w lemma="strong:G4521">day of the week</w>, <transChange type="tenseChange"><w lemma="strong:G2064">they came</w></transChange> <w lemma="strong:G3418">to the tomb</w> <w lemma="strong:G2246">when the sun</w> <w lemma="strong:G393">had risen</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.3"><w lemma="strong:G3004">They were saying</w> <w lemma="strong:G1438">to one</w> <w lemma="strong:G1438">another</w>, “<w lemma="strong:G5101">Who</w> <w lemma="strong:G617">will roll</w> <w lemma="strong:G617">away</w> <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.3.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.27.60">Matt 27:60</reference>; <reference osisRef="Mark.15.46">Mark 15:46</reference>; <reference osisRef="Mark.16.4">16:4</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G3037">the stone</w> <w lemma="strong:G2374">for us from the entrance</w> <w lemma="strong:G3419">of the tomb</w>?” </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.4"><w lemma="strong:G308">Looking</w> <transChange type="tenseChange"><w lemma="strong:G2334">up, they saw</w></transChange> <w lemma="strong:G3037">that the stone</w> <w lemma="strong:G352a">had been rolled</w> <w lemma="strong:G352a">away</w>, <note n="1" osisID="Mark.16.4.note.1" type="explanation">Lit <hi type="italic">for</hi></note><w lemma="strong:G1063">although</w> <w lemma="strong:G4970">it was extremely</w> <w lemma="strong:G3173">large</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.5"><note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.5.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="John.20.11">John 20:11</reference>, <reference osisRef="John.20.12">12</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G1525">Entering</w> <w lemma="strong:G3419">the tomb</w>, <w lemma="strong:G3708">they saw</w> <w lemma="strong:G3495">a young</w> <w lemma="strong:G3495">man</w> <w lemma="strong:G2521">sitting</w> <w lemma="strong:G1188">at the right</w>, <w lemma="strong:G4016">wearing</w> <w lemma="strong:G3022">a white</w> <w lemma="strong:G4749">robe</w>; and they <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.5.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.9.15">Mark 9:15</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G1568">were amazed</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.6"><transChange type="tenseChange"><w lemma="strong:G3004">And he said</w></transChange> to them, “<note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.6.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.9.15">Mark 9:15</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G1568">Do not be amazed</w>; <w lemma="strong:G2212">you are looking</w> <w lemma="strong:G2424">for Jesus</w> the <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.6.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.1.24">Mark 1:24</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G3479">Nazarene</w>, <w lemma="strong:G4717">who has been crucified</w>. <note n="C" osisID="Mark.16.6.xref.C" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.28.6">Matt 28:6</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.24.6">Luke 24:6</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G1453">He has risen</w>; <w lemma="strong:G5602">He is not here</w>; <w lemma="strong:G2396">behold</w>, <transChange type="added">here is</transChange> <w lemma="strong:G5117">the place</w> <w lemma="strong:G3699">where</w> <w lemma="strong:G5087">they laid</w> Him. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.7"><milestone marker="“" type="cQuote" /><w lemma="strong:G5217">But go</w>, <w lemma="strong:G3004">tell</w> <w lemma="strong:G3101">His disciples</w> <w lemma="strong:G4074">and Peter</w>, ‘<note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.7.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.26.32">Matt 26:32</reference>; <reference osisRef="Mark.14.28">Mark 14:28</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G4254">He is going</w> <w lemma="strong:G4254">ahead</w> <w lemma="strong:G1056">of you to Galilee</w>; <w lemma="strong:G1563">there</w> <w lemma="strong:G3708">you will see</w> <w lemma="strong:G2531a">Him, just</w> <w lemma="strong:G3004">as He told</w> you.’” </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.8"><w lemma="strong:G1831">They went</w> <w lemma="strong:G5343">out and fled</w> <w lemma="strong:G3419">from the tomb</w>, <w lemma="strong:G5156">for trembling</w> <w lemma="strong:G1611">and astonishment</w> <w lemma="strong:G2192">had gripped</w> <w lemma="strong:G3004">them; and they said</w> <w lemma="strong:G3762">nothing</w> <w lemma="strong:G3762">to anyone</w>, <w lemma="strong:G5399">for they were afraid</w>. <milestone subType="x-PM" type="line" /></verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.9">[<note n="1" osisID="Mark.16.9.note.1" type="explanation">Later mss add vv 9-20</note><w lemma="strong:G1161">Now</w> <w lemma="strong:G450">after He had risen</w> <w lemma="strong:G4404">early</w> <w lemma="strong:G4413">on the first</w> <w lemma="strong:G4521">day of the week</w>, <w lemma="strong:G4413">He first</w> <w lemma="strong:G5316">appeared</w> to <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.9.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.27.56">Matt 27:56</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.20.14">John 20:14</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G3137">Mary</w> <w lemma="strong:G3094">Magdalene</w>, <w lemma="strong:G3739">from whom</w> <w lemma="strong:G1544b">He had cast</w> <w lemma="strong:G2033">out seven</w> <w lemma="strong:G1140">demons</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.10"><note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.10.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="John.20.18">John 20:18</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G4198">She went</w> <w lemma="strong:G518">and reported</w> <w lemma="strong:G3588">to those</w> <w lemma="strong:G1096">who had been</w> <w lemma="strong:G3996">with Him, while they were mourning</w> <w lemma="strong:G2799">and weeping</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.11"><w lemma="strong:G191">When they heard</w> <w lemma="strong:G2198">that He was alive</w> <w lemma="strong:G2300">and had been seen</w> by her, <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.11.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.28.17">Matt 28:17</reference>; <reference osisRef="Mark.16.13">Mark 16:13</reference>, <reference osisRef="Mark.16.14">14</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.24.11">Luke 24:11</reference>, <reference osisRef="Luke.24.41">41</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.20.25">John 20:25</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G569">they refused</w> <w lemma="strong:G569">to believe</w> it. <milestone subType="x-PM" type="line" /></verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.12"><w lemma="strong:G3326">After</w> that, <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.12.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.16.14">Mark 16:14</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.21.1">John 21:1</reference>, <reference osisRef="John.21.14">14</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G5319">He appeared</w> <w lemma="strong:G2087">in a different</w> <w lemma="strong:G3444">form</w> <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.12.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Luke.24.13-Luke.24.35">Luke 24:13-35</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G1417">to two</w> <w lemma="strong:G4043">of them while they were walking</w> <w lemma="strong:G4198">along on their way</w> <w lemma="strong:G68">to the country</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.13"><w lemma="strong:G565">They went</w> <w lemma="strong:G565">away</w> <w lemma="strong:G518">and reported</w> <w lemma="strong:G3062">it to the others</w>, but they <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.13.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.28.17">Matt 28:17</reference>; <reference osisRef="Mark.16.11">Mark 16:11</reference>, <reference osisRef="Mark.16.14">14</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.24.11">Luke 24:11</reference>, <reference osisRef="Luke.24.41">41</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.20.25">John 20:25</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G4100">did not believe</w> <w lemma="strong:G3761">them either</w>. <milestone subType="x-PM" type="line" /></verse><div type="x-milestone" subType="x-preverse" sID="pv1769" /><title subType="x-preverse" type="section">The Disciples Commissioned</title> <div type="x-milestone" subType="x-preverse" eID="pv1769" /><verse osisID="Mark.16.14"><w lemma="strong:G5305">Afterward</w> <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.14.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.16.12">Mark 16:12</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.21.1">John 21:1</reference>, <reference osisRef="John.21.14">14</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G5319">He appeared</w> <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.14.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Luke.24.36">Luke 24:36</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.20.19">John 20:19</reference>, <reference osisRef="John.20.26">26</reference>; <reference osisRef="1Cor.15.5">1 Cor 15:5</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G1733">to the eleven</w> <w lemma="strong:G846">themselves</w> <w lemma="strong:G345">as they were reclining</w> <transChange type="added">at the table</transChange>; <w lemma="strong:G3679">and He reproached</w> them for their <note n="C" osisID="Mark.16.14.xref.C" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.28.17">Matt 28:17</reference>; <reference osisRef="Mark.16.11">Mark 16:11</reference>, <reference osisRef="Mark.16.13">13</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.24.11">Luke 24:11</reference>, <reference osisRef="Luke.24.41">41</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.20.25">John 20:25</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G570">unbelief</w> <w lemma="strong:G4641">and hardness</w> <w lemma="strong:G4641">of heart</w>, <w lemma="strong:G3754">because</w> <w lemma="strong:G4100">they had not believed</w> <w lemma="strong:G3588">those</w> <w lemma="strong:G2300">who had seen</w> <w lemma="strong:G1453">Him after He had risen</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.15"><w lemma="strong:G3004">And He said</w> to them, <q marker="" who="Jesus"><q sID="gen26871" />“<note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.15.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Matt.28.19">Matt 28:19</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.1.8">Acts 1:8</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G4198">Go</w> <w lemma="strong:G537a">into all</w> <w lemma="strong:G2889">the world</w> <w lemma="strong:G2784">and preach</w> <w lemma="strong:G2098">the gospel</w> <w lemma="strong:G3956">to all</w> <w lemma="strong:G2937">creation</w>.<q eID="gen26871" /></q> </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.16"><q marker="" who="Jesus"><q sID="gen26873" /><milestone marker="“" type="cQuote" /><note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.16.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="John.3.18">John 3:18</reference>, <reference osisRef="John.3.36">36</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.16.31">Acts 16:31</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G4100">He who has believed</w> <w lemma="strong:G907">and has been baptized</w> <w lemma="strong:G4982">shall be saved</w>; <w lemma="strong:G569">but he who has disbelieved</w> <w lemma="strong:G2632">shall be condemned</w>.<q eID="gen26873" /></q> </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.17"><q marker="" who="Jesus"><q sID="gen26875" /><milestone marker="“" type="cQuote" /><w lemma="strong:G3778">These</w> <note n="1" osisID="Mark.16.17.note.1" type="explanation">Or <hi type="italic">attesting miracles</hi></note><w lemma="strong:G4592">signs</w> <w lemma="strong:G3877">will accompany</w> <w lemma="strong:G3588">those</w> <w lemma="strong:G4100">who have believed</w>: <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.17.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.9.38">Mark 9:38</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.10.17">Luke 10:17</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.5.16">Acts 5:16</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.8.7">8:7</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.16.18">16:18</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.19.12">19:12</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G3686">in My name</w> <w lemma="strong:G1544b">they will cast</w> <w lemma="strong:G1140">out demons</w>, they will <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.17.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Acts.2.4">Acts 2:4</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.10.46">10:46</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.19.6">19:6</reference>; <reference osisRef="1Cor.12.10">1 Cor 12:10</reference>, <reference osisRef="1Cor.12.28">28</reference>, <reference osisRef="1Cor.12.30">30</reference>; <reference osisRef="1Cor.13.1">13:1</reference>; <reference osisRef="1Cor.14.2">14:2</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G2980">speak</w> <w lemma="strong:G2537">with new</w> <w lemma="strong:G1100">tongues</w>;<q eID="gen26875" /></q> </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.18"><q marker="" who="Jesus"><q sID="gen26877" />they will <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.18.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Luke.10.19">Luke 10:19</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.28.3-Acts.28.5">Acts 28:3-5</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G142">pick</w> <w lemma="strong:G3789">up serpents</w>, <w lemma="strong:G2579">and if</w> <w lemma="strong:G4095">they drink</w> <w lemma="strong:G5100">any</w> <w lemma="strong:G2286">deadly</w> <transChange type="added">poison</transChange>, <w lemma="strong:G984">it will not hurt</w> them; they will <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.18.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Mark.5.23">Mark 5:23</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G2007">lay</w> <w lemma="strong:G5495">hands</w> <w lemma="strong:G732">on the sick</w>, <w lemma="strong:G2192 strong:G2573">and they will recover</w>.”<q eID="gen26877" /></q> <milestone subType="x-PM" type="line" /></verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.19"><w lemma="strong:G3767">So</w> <w lemma="strong:G3767">then</w>, <w lemma="strong:G2962">when the Lord</w> <w lemma="strong:G2424">Jesus</w> had <note n="A" osisID="Mark.16.19.xref.A" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Acts.1.3">Acts 1:3</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G2980">spoken</w> to them, He <note n="B" osisID="Mark.16.19.xref.B" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Luke.9.51">Luke 9:51</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.24.51">24:51</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.6.62">John 6:62</reference>; <reference osisRef="John.20.17">20:17</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.1.2">Acts 1:2</reference>, <reference osisRef="Acts.1.9-Acts.1.11">9-11</reference>; <reference osisRef="1Tim.3.16">1 Tim 3:16</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G353">was received</w> <w lemma="strong:G3772">up into heaven</w> and <note n="C" osisID="Mark.16.19.xref.C" type="crossReference"><reference osisRef="Ps.110.1">Ps 110:1</reference>; <reference osisRef="Luke.22.69">Luke 22:69</reference>; <reference osisRef="Acts.7.55-Acts.7.56">Acts 7:55f</reference>; <reference osisRef="Rom.8.34">Rom 8:34</reference>; <reference osisRef="Eph.1.20">Eph 1:20</reference>; <reference osisRef="Col.3.1">Col 3:1</reference>; <reference osisRef="Heb.1.3">Heb 1:3</reference>; <reference osisRef="Heb.8.1">8:1</reference>; <reference osisRef="Heb.10.12">10:12</reference>; <reference osisRef="Heb.12.2">12:2</reference>; <reference osisRef="1Pet.3.22">1 Pet 3:22</reference></note><w lemma="strong:G2523">sat</w> <w lemma="strong:G2523">down</w> <w lemma="strong:G1188">at the right</w> <w lemma="strong:G1188">hand</w> <w lemma="strong:G2316">of God</w>. </verse><verse osisID="Mark.16.20"><w lemma="strong:G1831">And they went</w> <w lemma="strong:G2784">out and preached</w> <w lemma="strong:G3837">everywhere</w>, <w lemma="strong:G2962">while the Lord</w> <w lemma="strong:G4903">worked</w> <w lemma="strong:G950">with them, and confirmed</w> <w lemma="strong:G3056">the word</w> by the <note n="1" osisID="Mark.16.20.note.1" type="explanation">Or <hi type="italic">attesting miracles</hi></note><w lemma="strong:G4592">signs</w> <w lemma="strong:G1872">that followed</w>.] <milestone subType="x-PM" type="line" /> [<note n="2" osisID="Mark.16.20.note.2" type="explanation">A few late mss and versions contain this paragraph, usually after v 8; a few have it at the end of ch</note><transChange type="added"><w lemma="strong:G3326">And they promptly reported all these instructions to Peter and his companions. And after</w> that, Jesus Himself sent out through them from east to west the sacred and imperishable proclamation of eternal salvation</transChange>.] <chapter eID="gen26855" osisID="Mark.16" /><div eID="gen25883" osisID="Mark" type="book" /></verse></div>
